#!/usr/bin/env bash
#
# Author: James Cherti
# URL: https://github.com/jamescherti/jc-dev
#
# Description: Initialize and enter a chroot environment safely.
#              This script validates the target directory, verifies root
#              privileges, and binds essential system directories (dev,
#              proc, sys, run) before dropping into an interactive shell.
#              It implements an EXIT trap to guarantee that all bind mounts
#              are cleanly unmounted when the user exits the chroot session.
#
# Usage: ./chroot_enter.sh <chroot_directory>
#
